statement:
Suppose the interaction between two species ($x=x(t)$ is the âpreyâ
while $y=y(t)$ is the predator) can be modelled by the autonomous
system:

\begin{align*}\left\{
\begin{array}{c}
\frac{dx}{dt} = x\left(3-x-y\right) \\
\frac{dy}{dt} = y\left(1+x-y\right)
\end{array}
\right.\end{align*}

(a) Determine all the critical points and classify their type and
stability.

hints:
